Consider a two-player zero-sum game where player 1 has two strategies and player 2 has three strategies. The payoff matrix for the game is given by 

\begin{bmatrix}
3 & 2 & 1 \\
-2 & 1 & 4 \\
\end{bmatrix}

Player 1 chooses either strategy 1 or strategy 2, while player 2 chooses either strategy A, B or C. Find the optimal strategies for each player and the value of the game.
